# Beamer presentation and export workflow

When editing this repo (presentation.tex, create_prez.md, or the export scripts), follow these rules.

## Layout (create_prez.md)

1. **Image beside text**: On slides with body text and a figure, put the image to the right of the text (side by side), not below. Use `\begin{columns}[T]` with left column ~0.50\textwidth (text) and right column ~0.47\textwidth (figure).
2. **Text above footer**: Keep body text from overlapping the footer. Use `\vspace{-0.4em}` at the start of the frame; limit figure height (e.g. `height=0.58\textheight`); use `{\small ...}` for long equations.
3. **Same layout**: Use the same side-by-side column layout on every slide that has one main figure and one text block.
4. **Always compile at the end**: After any change to the presentation, run `pdflatex -interaction=nonstopmode presentation.tex`.

## Style

- Avoid em dashes (—); use colons or sub-bullets instead.
- Avoid bold mid-sentence; use bold only for labels (e.g. **Topic**:, **Goal**:) at the start of items.

## Logo

- Optional footer logo: add `logo.png` in the repo folder and in `presentation.tex` uncomment:
  `\renewcommand{\mylogo}{\includegraphics[height=0.45cm]{logo.png}}`

## Workflow order

1. Edit `presentation.tex`
2. Compile PDF: `pdflatex -interaction=nonstopmode presentation.tex`
3. Export PNGs: `python3 export_slides.py`
4. Build PPTX: `python3 slides_to_pptx.py`

Do not skip recompiling the PDF after .tex changes before re-exporting images or PPTX.
